          <Comment>For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 496744). This variant is also known as c.496delA. This premature translational stop signal has been observed in individuals with poikiloderma with neutropenia (PMID: 21271650). This variant is not present in population databases (gnomAD no frequency). This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Thr167Profs*98) in the USB1 gene. While this is not anticipated to result in nonsense mediated decay, it is expected to disrupt the last 99 amino acid(s) of the USB1 protein.</Comment>
